inta, Para _s_ ara, Vish\n_n_ u, Rudra, Skanda, Ka _s_ i _s_ vara, _G_ vara, Dharma, Artha, Kama,\nKrodha, Vasish _th_ a, Indra, Tvash _t_ _ri_ , Kart _ri_ , Dhart _ri_ , Dhat\n_ri_ , M _ri_ tyu, Savit _ri_ , Savitri, and for each Veda, for the _Ri_\ng-veda, the Ya _g_ ur-veda, the Sama-veda, the Atharva-veda, the Itihasa and\nPura _n_ a.\n\n7\\. Towards the south, with their sacrificial cords suspended over their right\nshoulders, in a place inclined towards the south, they arrange seats of\nsouthward-pointed Darbha grass, so that they end in the west\xc2\x97\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[243:1](sbe30091.htm#fr_706) 19, 1. According to Mat _ri_ datta, they prepare\na seat for Brahman with the words, 'For Brahman I prepare (a seat),' and so\non. Comp. chap. 20, 3.\n\n[244:2](sbe30091.htm#fr_707) This is a frequently quoted versus memorialis.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: II, 8, 20](sbe30092.htm)\n\n"